  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Restoring livelihoods of vulnerable populations to catastrophic food and nutrition insecurity in Borno, Adamawa and Yobe States</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving agriculture assistance to internally displaced people, host community members and returnees in Northeast Nigeria. This FAO project provides essential agricultural inputs such as seeds and fertilizer, establishes farmer field schools, provides livestock inputs such as poultry and goats, distributes fuel efficient stoves, provides fresh food vouchers to enable households to access a diversity of fresh and nutrition foods from FAO-supported farmers. The project provides life-saving assistance to 130,000 people, including 30,600 women, 25,500 men, 73,900 children, and 2,600 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
